The paper introduces a new approach for learning generative models over graphs using graph neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), and social and information networks (cs.SI). The paper specifically focuses on the use of deep learning techniques for generative modeling of graphs, which is a popular area of research in the machine learning community, hence the high likelihood of the paper belonging to cs.LG and cs.AI. The paper also discusses the application of the proposed approach to molecular graphs, which is a common use case in computer vision and natural language processing, hence the likelihood of the paper belonging to cs.CV and cs.CL. Finally, the paper discusses the use of graph neural networks for modeling relational data structures, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
